title: For Sale:  Mauser P08 Luger Black Widow Semi Automatic Pistol 1941
postcontent:
This is the nicest example I have ever seen of a Mauser P08 Luger Black Widow Semi Automatic Pistol 1941
This is a 1941 Pistole 08 military gun manufactured by Mauser. This piece is a 4 inch (98 mm) 9mm Parabellum.  To conceal production a series of alphabetical/numbers were assigned to Mauser in 1939 to identify their production in addition to the date code over the chamber to indicate the year of production. In February 1941 Mauser changed from the 42 code to byf.   ''41" dates are representative of the Luger contract production accepted by the German military in 1941.
This is a standard 1934 Model gun designated by collectors as the "Black Widow" 41/42 Mauser. This Luger has all matching numbers.

The finish is 96% Blued and no straw blue on this model and model has a hold open latch and stock lug..

The first toggle link is marked with the "42" Mauser code.  There is the "V" rear sight on the rear toggle link and the last two digits of the serial number appear.

This variation (41/42) in the black widow is a difficult gun for the Mauser collector to obtain. 

The pictures don't do it justice, you will not be disappointed.
$2500 OBO

title: For Trade:  Tactical Colt M4 carbine 22 AR15
postcontent:
Back on the market!
Had a trade agreement for this rifle set to take place this morning, however the gentleman I was trading with decided to cancel as his firearms [apparently] had sentimental value to him. Been in the situation before and I'm glad he pulled out rather than regretting his trade.

I'm willing to sell for cash but want to review all trade offers first.

It is a Colt M4 Carbine AR15 weapon chambered in .22lr.
I actually think it makes a GREAT defense weapon, one that my wife feels very comfortable handling. 
However its purpose is to familiarize yourself with ar15 combat. 

.223/5.56 ammo is drying up and nobody can afford to blow through their stock pile at the range.
However if you expect to be confident handling your weapon you need to spend lots of time shooting it, 1000 rnds downrange or more.

This Colt M4 shoots .22lr - the only ammunition you can find reliably and costs about 10x's less than .223 (I think you can still buy 550rnd value packs at walmart for under $20)

It is the exact same size and weight of a Colt M4 chambered for .223. 

One of the reasons I feel this makes a good defense weapon is the .22lr round's tendency to 'roll' or 'tumble' when it enters a target (take a zig-zag path through a body, often ricocheting off bone and hard tissue finding its way through vital organs) 

Colt comes with tactical forearm, adjustable stock and 30rnd magazine.

The Lee Deluxe Rifle 3 Die set is perfect for the beginning or experienced reloader. The set is made of steel and includes a full length sizing die, collet neck sizing die and bullet seating die. Use the full length sizing die to produce ammunition to factory-new specifications using cases fired in other guns. The collet neck sizing die will allow you to produce ammunition that is fire-formed to the chamber of one rifle.

Lee Precision has been producing some of the highest quality reloading equipment for over 50 years. Their Deluxe 3-Die Sets for rifle cartridges are no different. They are made to tight tolerances to help reloaders make consistent and accurate ammunition. These die sets are perfect for both beginning and seasoned reloaders. Each die is made of steel and the set comes with a full length sizing die, collet neck sizing die and bullet seating die. Reloaders use the full length sizing die to produce ammunition to factory-new specifications using new brass or brass cases that were fired in other guns. Full length sizing dies are also great for the reloader who wants to ensure each round loaded will chamber in their rifle with ease. The collet neck sizing die allows reloaders to product ammunition that has been fire-formed to the chamber of that rifle. Since only the neck is sized more force may be required to get each round to chamber but brass life is extended and a lot of reloaders see an increase in accuracy. This set also includes a bullet seating die, shellholder, powder dipper, storage box and load data.

title: For Sale:  Underwood .45 Super 230gr. Gold Dot JHP
location: Southport Rd and Emerson Rd, Indianapolis, Indiana
postcontent:
I have 43 (50 minus 7 rounds that I shot through my .45) rounds of Underwood .45 Super 230gr. Gold Dot JHP's for sale.  If you don't know what .45 Super is, it's a wildcat round that was invented to be run through normal .45ACP guns.  This ammo capitalizes on the massive case volume that the .45ACP round has by thickening the web area of the casing to withstand much much higher pressures translating into much higher velocities and kinetic energy than any .45ACP +P rounds can produce.  I was running this ammo through my Glock 36 with upgraded 23lb. springs.  I never had a single malfunction in the 200 rounds of .45 Super I ran through it.  I wouldn't suggest this ammo for lower end .45ACP's (i.e. Taurus, cheaper 1911's, Hi Points, etc.) as these cheaper guns likely don't have the case head support for this increased pressure.  All that to say, this ammo is the ultimate .45 defensive ammo that you can run without getting a custom barrel or putting a compensator on your gun.  Please call or text if you are interested or have any questions at two60-four03-01seven2

Specifications:
230gr. JHP Gold Dot
1100 fps
618 ft. lbs.
